<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,925,1238]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,304,925,950]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Remark.</emphasis>
Males taken in the same area as the 
<typeStatus box="[716,814,925,950]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">holotype</typeStatus>
but in an older cultivated plot (
<number box="[1169,1198,926,950]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="23.0">23</number>
years old after being abandoned) or in mature forest (Monte alta) show distinct genitalia, with shorter median lophi, and a more contrasted pattern of coloration, which could justify describing them as a distinct species. Females from the same plots have a short subgenital plate with acute distal angles (
<figureCitation box="[850,920,1033,1058]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="16.[151,249,1252,1274]" captionTargetBox="[159,1431,197,1225]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,193,1230]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 7. Zebragryllus Desutter-Grandcolas and Cadena-Castañeda, n. gen.: Female subgenital plate (ventral, lateral) and copulatory papilla (dorsal, ventral, lateral) in: Zebragryllus sp. affinis fuscus Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. (A – D), Z. intermedius Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. (E – I); Z. nauta Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. (J – N). Scales 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285599/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
Fig. 
<number box="[906,920,1034,1058]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
A, B) and a very distinct copulatory papilla, subrectangular with concave distal margin (
<figureCitation box="[640,706,1069,1094]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="16.[151,249,1252,1274]" captionTargetBox="[159,1431,197,1225]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,193,1230]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 7. Zebragryllus Desutter-Grandcolas and Cadena-Castañeda, n. gen.: Female subgenital plate (ventral, lateral) and copulatory papilla (dorsal, ventral, lateral) in: Zebragryllus sp. affinis fuscus Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. (A – D), Z. intermedius Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. (E – I); Z. nauta Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. (J – N). Scales 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285599/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
Fig. 
<number box="[692,706,1070,1094]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
C, D).
</paragraph>
